passages.text: Our daily analytics package and commentary on global inflation markets.

The US RY curve continued to steepen on Tuesday, as 5y yields fell 5bp while 30y yields were up 1bp. US cash breakevens and inflation swaps were 1- 3bp higher. Data this week include the second release of Q2 GDP (Thu), July core PCE inflation (Fri), and the final release of August UMich consumer sentiment (Fri). Friday is month- end, and Bloomberg projects the duration extension of the 1- 30y Series- L TIPS index to be 0.08y, in line with our estimate from earlier this month.

EUR real yield curves steepened on Tuesday, with sub- 10y RYs falling 3bp and back- end RYs rising 1- 2bp. Cash breakevens were up 1- 2bp. In swaps HICPx and FRCPix gained 2bp in sub- 5y, and 1bp in the 5y- 15y area. In data this week, flash August inflation prints will be released for Germany, France, Spain and Italy (all Fri, see August HICP preview). Also scheduled are the EC survey (Thu) and the ECB's CES survey (Fri). The ECB's Rehn (Thu) and Guindos (Fri) are speaking this week. Also, the minutes of the July ECB meeting will be released on Thursday. No EUR IL supply is scheduled this week. Friday is month- end. Bloomberg estimates the EUR IL series- B index duration extension at 0.01y.

UK real yields were close to unchanged on Tuesday, while UK breakevens and RPI swaps trimmed 1- 2bp, leaving iotas slightly wider. In supply, the next UK linker auction is due on 4 September, when the DMO will issue IL45. Friday is month- end. Bloomberg estimates the UK IL series- B index duration extension at - 0.02y.
